qas.question: What estuary east of Plymouth is part of the River Plym?
When did the Plymouth Breakwater open?
What island is present in Plymouth Sound?
How large is the Unitary Authority of Plymouth in square miles?
In meters, what is the highest point in the Plymouth Unitary Authority?

context: The River Plym, which flows off Dartmoor to the north-east, forms a smaller estuary to the east of the city called <a0_0>Cattewater<a0_0/>. Plymouth Sound is protected from the sea by the Plymouth Breakwater, in use since <a1_0>1814<a1_0/>. In the Sound is <a2_0>Drake's Island<a2_0/> which is seen from Plymouth Hoe, a flat public area on top of limestone cliffs. The Unitary Authority of Plymouth is 79.84 square kilometres (<a3_0>30.83<a3_0/> sq mi). The topography rises from sea level to a height, at Roborough, of about 509 feet (<a4_0>155<a4_0/> m) above Ordnance Datum (AOD).
